text.tspan: E-mail: Note: These numbers are only applicable after the Emergency Response Team has been activated.Pertinent ship’s drawings, instruction books, manuals, etc are available at all the above locations and they are also provided withrequisite response facilities such as conference phone, direct fax, computer network, whiteboard, vessel`s information and all requiredcontact info.7.2.3DUTY SUPERINTENDENTOn a weekly basis the company’s 24 hrs emergency contact mobile phone shall be rotated among the company’sSuperintendents. The number is in a cascade system where in case the phone is switched off, out of range or not answered, the call isdiverted to the General Manager.The superintendent handling this mobile phone is called Duty superintendent. When carrying/ handling the emergency mobile the dutysuperintendent shall ensure that:a. He does not consume alcohol.b. He remains within one hour travel time from the office.c. He does not make any outgoing calls using the Emergency phone.d. He physically carries the Mobile phone and does not use call forwarding.e. He carries a print out of the “Emergency Notification Directory – EP 1”.The person receiving the initial emergency report shall immediately mobilize the Emergency Response Team (ERT) using theinformation from “Emergency Notification Directory – EP 1”.7.2.4EMERGENCY RESPONSE TEAM (ERT)The Emergency Response Team (ERT) reports to the Managing Director and consists of the following entities/ functions:1. Incident Commander2. Emergency Response Advice3. Media Handling4. Business Continuity5. Technical Support6. Technical Advice7. Logistics8. Navigation and Cargo9. HR Support10. IT (Information Technology)11. Field Team12. TravelIn consultation with the Managing Director, the Incident Commander shall decide whether the situation warrants the assembly of theentire ERT or a smaller team.Upon assembly the ERT will be given a thorough briefing by the Duty Officer, who will thereafter defer to the Incident Commander. ERT shall ensure that the office checklist OQ11 is complied with.If necessary, additional support staff such as Secretaries, Receptionist, IT System administrator, Purchaser etc., should be called in.A Field team will be identified and prepared to travel to the vessel/ port in order to set up a Field Command Post if required.Once the initial response and notification has been done and it seems that the incident will be a prolonged one, a duty cycle shall beestablished based on the availability of staff.The Managing Director will be kept informed of the events by the ERT.Note: For vessel's under Malaysian DOC functions of:1. Incident Commander2. Technical Support
